\pard\b\fs30 1. Abstract\b0\fs24\par
\par
\pard The Academic Transcript Generation System is a Java Swing desktop application developed to help a registrar record student course results and generate academic transcripts. The system stores student details, semester records, courses, scores, grades, grade points, semester GPA, cumulative GPA, and degree classification. It applies Object Oriented Programming principles such as encapsulation, inheritance, polymorphism, and abstraction through a well-structured class design.\par
\par
\pard The application provides a graphical user interface where the registrar logs in, selects or adds a student, enters course results, and views an official or unofficial transcript. It also supports transcript printing and text export. The system demonstrates modular programming by separating the project into model, service, formatter, exception, and graphical user interface packages.\par
\par
\pard\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw10\brsp20\par\pard\par
\par
\pard\b\fs30 2. Introduction\b0\fs24\par
\par
\pard Academic institutions need accurate and organized systems for processing student results. A transcript is an important academic document because it summarizes a student's courses, grades, GPA, CGPA, and classification. Manual transcript preparation can lead to errors in calculation, missing records, and delays.\par
\par
\pard This project was developed as an Object Oriented Programming practical application. It uses Java Swing for the graphical user interface and Java classes to model real-world academic objects such as students, courses, semester records, course results, and transcripts.\par
\par
\pard The project focuses on showing how OOP concepts can be used to solve a real academic record problem in a clean and understandable way.\par
\par
\pard\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw10\brsp20\par\pard\par
\par
\pard\b\fs30 3. Problem Statement\b0\fs24\par
\par
\pard Many transcript processes require repeated manual calculations. This can create the following problems:\par
\par
\pard\li360\fi-180 ? Wrong GPA or CGPA calculations.\par\pard
\pard\li360\fi-180 ? Difficulty organizing course results by semester.\par\pard
\pard\li360\fi-180 ? Repetition when preparing transcript records.\par\pard
\pard\li360\fi-180 ? Poor validation of student details, scores, and credit hours.\par\pard
\pard\li360\fi-180 ? Lack of a simple interface for entering and viewing transcript information.\par\pard
\par
\pard The Academic Transcript Generation System addresses these problems by automating result entry, grade conversion, GPA calculation, CGPA calculation, classification, and transcript display.\par
\par
\pard\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw10\brsp20\par\pard\par
\par
\pard\b\fs30 4. Aim and Objectives\b0\fs24\par
\par
\pard\b\fs26 Aim\b0\fs24\par
\par
\pard The aim of this project is to design and implement an Academic Transcript Generation System using Java Swing and Object Oriented Programming principles.\par
\par
\pard\b\fs26 Objectives\b0\fs24\par
\par
\pard The objectives are to:\par
\par
\pard\li360 1. Create a registrar login interface.\par\pard
\pard\li360 2. Allow the registrar to add and select students.\par\pard
\pard\li360 3. Allow course results to be added under semesters.\par\pard
\pard\li360 4. Convert raw scores into grades and grade points.\par\pard
\pard\li360 5. Calculate semester GPA automatically.\par\pard
\pard\li360 6. Calculate cumulative GPA across all semesters.\par\pard
\pard\li360 7. Determine degree classification from CGPA.\par\pard
\pard\li360 8. Display transcript information in official and unofficial formats.\par\pard
\pard\li360 9. Demonstrate OOP concepts in a working Java application.\par\pard
\pard\li360 10. Provide a simple way to print or export transcript information.\par\pard
\par
\pard\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw10\brsp20\par\pard\par
\par
\pard\b\fs30 5. Scope of the System\b0\fs24\par
\par
\pard The system covers the following functions:\par
\par
\pard\li360\fi-180 ? Registrar authentication.\par\pard
\pard\li360\fi-180 ? Student record management.\par\pard
\pard\li360\fi-180 ? Course result entry.\par\pard
\pard\li360\fi-180 ? Core and elective course classification.\par\pard
\pard\li360\fi-180 ? Raw score to grade conversion.\par\pard
\pard\li360\fi-180 ? GPA and CGPA calculation.\par\pard
\pard\li360\fi-180 ? Degree classification.\par\pard
\pard\li360\fi-180 ? Transcript viewing.\par\pard
\pard\li360\fi-180 ? Transcript printing.\par\pard
\pard\li360\fi-180 ? Transcript text export.\par\pard
\par
\pard The system is designed as a desktop application. It uses in-memory data storage, meaning that data entered during a session is available while the application is running. A future version can add database storage.\par
\par
