\par
\pard\b\fs26 7.2 Main Packages\b0\fs24\par
\par
\pard | Package | Purpose |\par
\pard |---|---|\par
\pard | model | Contains the main domain classes such as Student, Course, SemesterRecord, and Transcript. |\par
\pard | service | Contains business logic such as login, GPA services, classification, and student repository operations. |\par
\pard | formatter | Contains transcript formatting classes. |\par
\pard | exception | Contains the custom validation exception. |\par
\pard | gui | Contains Java Swing user interface classes. |\par
\par
\pard\b\fs26 7.3 System Flow\b0\fs24\par
\par
\pard\li360 1. Registrar opens the application.\par\pard
\pard\li360 2. Registrar logs in with username and PIN.\par\pard
\pard\li360 3. Registrar selects an existing student or adds a new student.\par\pard
\pard\li360 4. Registrar adds course results for a semester.\par\pard
\pard\li360 5. The system converts the score to a grade.\par\pard
\pard\li360 6. The system calculates quality points, GPA, CGPA, and classification.\par\pard
\pard\li360 7. Registrar views the transcript.\par\pard
\pard\li360 8. Registrar prints or exports the transcript.\par\pard
\par
\pard\b\fs26 7.4 GPA and CGPA Formula\b0\fs24\par
\par
\pard For each course:\par
\par
\f1\fs20 Quality Points = Grade Point * Credit Hours\par
\par
\pard For a semester:\par
\par
\f1\fs20 Semester GPA = Total Quality Points for Semester / Total Semester Credit Hours\par
\par
\pard For all semesters:\par
\par
\f1\fs20 CGPA = Total Quality Points Across All Semesters / Total Credit Hours Across All Semesters\par
\par
\pard\b\fs26 7.5 Degree Classification\b0\fs24\par
\par
\pard | CGPA Range | Classification |\par
\pard |---|---|\par
\pard | 3.60 and above | First Class |\par
\pard | 3.00 to 3.59 | Second Class Upper |\par
\pard | 2.50 to 2.99 | Second Class Lower |\par
\pard | 2.00 to 2.49 | Third Class |\par
\pard | Below 2.00 | Pass / Fail |\par
\par
