\pard\b\fs30 8. Object Oriented Programming Concepts Applied\b0\fs24\par
\par
\pard\b\fs26 8.1 Encapsulation\b0\fs24\par
\par
\pard Encapsulation is used by making class fields private and providing public methods to access them. Examples include:\par
\par
\pard\li360\fi-180 ? `Course` stores `code`, `title`, and `creditHours` as private fields.\par\pard
\pard\li360\fi-180 ? `Student` stores `id`, `name`, `programme`, and semester records as private fields.\par\pard
\pard\li360\fi-180 ? `CourseResult` stores the course, score, and grade as private fields.\par\pard
\par
\pard This prevents direct uncontrolled access to object data.\par
\par
\pard\b\fs26 8.2 Inheritance\b0\fs24\par
\par
\pard Inheritance is used through the Course class hierarchy.\par
\par
\f1\fs20 Course\par
\f1\fs20   CoreCourse\par
\f1\fs20   ElectiveCourse\par
\par
\pard CoreCourse and ElectiveCourse inherit common course properties from Course but provide their own course category.\par
\par
\pard\b\fs26 8.3 Polymorphism\b0\fs24\par
\par
\pard Polymorphism is used in two main places:\par
\par
\pard\li360 1. `getCategory()` is implemented differently in `CoreCourse` and `ElectiveCourse`.\par\pard
\pard\li360 2. `TranscriptFormatter` has different implementations:\par\pard
\pard    - OfficialTranscriptFormatter\par
\pard    - UnofficialTranscriptFormatter\par
\par
\pard The GUI can call formatter.format(transcript) without needing to know the exact formatter implementation.\par
\par
\pard\b\fs26 8.4 Abstraction\b0\fs24\par
\par
\pard Abstraction is used through:\par
\par
\pard\li360\fi-180 ? The abstract `Course` class.\par\pard
\pard\li360\fi-180 ? The `TranscriptFormatter` interface.\par\pard
\par
\pard These hide implementation details and define what subclasses or implementations must provide.\par
\par
\pard\b\fs26 8.5 Exception Handling\b0\fs24\par
\par
\pard The system uses a custom checked exception named InvalidInputException. It is thrown when invalid input is detected, such as:\par
\par
\pard\li360\fi-180 ? Blank student ID.\par\pard
\pard\li360\fi-180 ? Blank student name.\par\pard
\pard\li360\fi-180 ? Credit hours less than or equal to zero.\par\pard
\pard\li360\fi-180 ? Score outside 0 to 100.\par\pard
\pard\li360\fi-180 ? Wrong registrar login details.\par\pard
\par
\pard The GUI catches the exception and displays the message using JOptionPane.\par
\par
\pard\b\fs26 8.6 Collections\b0\fs24\par
\par
\pard The system uses ArrayList to store:\par
\par
\pard\li360\fi-180 ? Students in `StudentRepository`.\par\pard
\pard\li360\fi-180 ? Semester records in `Student`.\par\pard
\pard\li360\fi-180 ? Course results in `SemesterRecord`.\par\pard
\par
\pard\b\fs26 8.7 Event Handling\b0\fs24\par
\par
\pard Swing action listeners are used for button actions such as login, adding a student, adding a course result, viewing a transcript, printing, and exporting.\par
\par
\pard\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw10\brsp20\par\pard\par
\par
\pard\b\fs30 9. Implementation Details\b0\fs24\par
\par
\pard\b\fs26 9.1 Main Class\b0\fs24\par
\par
\pard Main.java starts the application. It launches the Swing interface using SwingUtilities.invokeLater() so the GUI runs on the Event Dispatch Thread.\par
\par
\pard\b\fs26 9.2 Model Classes\b0\fs24\par
\par
\pard | Class | Description |\par
\pard |---|---|\par
\pard | Course | Abstract parent class for all course types. |\par
\pard | CoreCourse | Represents a core course. |\par
\pard | ElectiveCourse | Represents an elective course. |\par
\pard | Grade | Enum that maps scores to grade points. |\par
\pard | CourseResult | Combines a course with the score and grade earned. |\par
\pard | SemesterRecord | Stores all course results for one semester. |\par
\pard | Student | Stores student details and semester records. |\par
\pard | Transcript | Calculates CGPA and classification for a student. |\par
\par
\pard\b\fs26 9.3 Service Classes\b0\fs24\par
\par
\pard | Class | Description |\par
\pard |---|---|\par
\pard | AuthService | Validates registrar login. |\par
\pard | StudentRepository | Stores demo students and added students in memory. |\par
\pard | GpaService | Provides GPA and CGPA helper methods. |\par
\pard | ClassificationService | Maps CGPA to classification. |\par
\par
\pard\b\fs26 9.4 Formatter Classes\b0\fs24\par
\par
\pard | Class | Description |\par
\pard |---|---|\par
\pard | TranscriptFormatter | Interface for transcript output formatting. |\par
\pard | OfficialTranscriptFormatter | Produces a detailed official transcript layout. |\par
\pard | UnofficialTranscriptFormatter | Produces a short GPA summary. |\par
\par
\pard\b\fs26 9.5 GUI Classes\b0\fs24\par
\par
\pard | Class | Description |\par
\pard |---|---|\par
\pard | MainFrame | Main Swing frame with login, student, result, and transcript screens. |\par
\pard | AppTheme | Centralizes colors, fonts, and button styles. |\par
